    <h2>Welcome to GoFundUIT!</h2>
    <p>Starting your fundraiser is an important step — and we’re here to help you make it impactful. Below are detailed tips to get you going with confidence:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Create a clear and personal title:</strong> Use names and keywords that help others understand the cause immediately.</li>
      <li><strong>Write a compelling story:</strong> Break your story into short paragraphs. Explain who needs help, why, how the money will be used, and why it matters.</li>
      <li><strong>Use high-quality images:</strong> A bright, positive photo of you or the cause can inspire more donations.</li>
      <li><strong>Set a realistic goal:</strong> Be honest about what you need — people are more likely to give when goals feel achievable.</li>
      <li><strong>Share regularly:</strong> Post updates, thank donors, and keep your community informed. Use Facebook, Instagram, and personal messages.</li>
      <li><strong>Stay safe:</strong> Avoid offers to “boost” your fundraiser for money. If something seems too good to be true, it probably is.</li>
    </ul>

